title: I bought a designer 1990s Fendi bag from a charity shop for £200 on a hunch it's worth far more - am I right? DAN HATFIELD replies

description: Change, change, change, intoned winning Labour candidates, robotically on message as they claimed their party was the agent of revolution. But was the true catalyst the light-blue lot?
title: QUENTIN LETTS: London pundits analysed Farage's party like chimps confronted by a Rubik's Cube

description: When it comes to affairs, men can be lazy and predictable, so often transferring their affections to someone close at hand; if it's not the PA or the nanny, it could be their wife's best friend.
title: The eight signs your friend fancies your husband, revealed by a top psychotherapist... who also tells what to do if you suspect her

description: Nick Robinson will not thank me for reminding readers that just before the result of the 2010 Labour leadership election was announced, he said that David Miliband was about to emerge victorious.
title: TOM UTLEY: I haven't voted for a winning candidate for 44 years. But I love everything about the polling booth - starting with the pencil stub on the end of a string!

description: Call me a hopeless optimist but, on the train to the Television and Radio Industries Club Awards last week, I felt so excited that I was rehearsing our team's acceptance speech in my head.
title: Millions watch Homes Under The Hammer and it's been going for 20 years. So why, asks presenter Martin Roberts, after 1,500 episodes have we NEVER won a single award?

description: Peter was in his car when his daughter Freya* called him, saying memories had 'come up'. Since receiving therapy for anxiety, Freya had said she remembered her grandfather raping her as a child.
title: Horror of being accused of rape by your daughter after a therapist helped her 'recover' a false memory

description: ALISON BOSHOFF: The actor has been renting both a townhouse and an art studio in London 's West End and is now throwing himself into his sideline as an artist.

description: RICHARD EDEN: King Charles has demonstrated that he is fully back in charge after his cancer treatment by taking the reins of a business which controls his Balmoral estate.
title: RICHARD EDEN: King Charles takes on unique role as boss of Balmoral

description: PATRICK MARMION: There are are few shows more difficult to describe, and even fewer that have left a deeper impression on me, than Complicité Theatre Company's magical production.
title: Mnemonic review: A magical, mercurial game-changer returns 25 years on, writes PATRICK MARMION

description: None of the Beverly Hills Cop sequels have matched the original, and the same is true of this latest Netflix effort, the first for 30 years. And yet it's genuine fun, all the same.
title: Beverly Hills Cop: Axel F review: A pleasing nostalgia trip, writes BRIAN VINER

description: Taking its cue from The Ramones' self-titled debut LP, Kasabian's Happenings lasts a shade under 29 minutes, pipping The Ramones by seconds in terms of lean, clean economy.
